    "updated_at": "2015-10-10T02:59:17Z",
    "body": "I'm :+1: on all of them, the purpose of introducing `--enable-logging` was exactly to disable Chromium's logging by default and only print `console.log` outputs in the main process.\n\nOn Windows the way Node implemented `process.stdout` and `console.log` doesn't work well in Electron, so we redirected them to use Chromium's logging system, that's why we have this issue and #2390, we need to fix that to solve all the problems.\n\n> I think the default behavior when running without --enable-logging should be to not output any logs including errors\n\nChromium hard-coded the logging system to always output `ERROR` logs, we have to patch Chromium to fix this.\n"
  },
